The paper discusses patterns for programming microservices, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE). The specific patterns discussed, circuit breaker, service discovery, and API gateway, are commonly used in distributed systems and therefore further support the likelihood of cs.DC being a relevant sub-category. The paper also evaluates the applicability of a specific programming language, Jolie, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper presents considerations for future developments, which could potentially fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY) if discussing improvements to the overall system architecture.
